The White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs and the Office of Public Engagement recently hosted a "Communities in Action" event, where nearly 60 local elected officials and community leaders from North Dakota, South Dakota, and Nebraska participated. Senior Biden-Harris Administration officials, such as Secretary of Agriculture Tom Vilsack, Director of the Office of Intergovernmental Affairs Tom Perez, and National Climate Advisor Ali Zaidi, spoke about the impacts of the American Rescue Plan, Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, and Inflation Reduction Act in their states. The officials emphasized the administration's efforts to collaborate with various stakeholders to utilize these investments for the benefit of working families. The participants also provided updates on how the administration's policies are addressing concerns in their communities, including food security, housing, and mental health parity. This event was part of a series of "Communities in Action" events aimed at showcasing the Biden-Harris Administration's achievements for the American people.